OL,3,COverpaying for overcrowding? Almost a
OL,4,Cquarter of train users have to stand
OL,6,FData from the Department for Transport
OL,7,F(DfT) has shown that of the 1.7
OL,8,Fbillion journeys taken by rail in
OL,9,FGreat Britain, almost 22% of
OL,10,Fpassengers are having to stand during
OL,11,Fmorning peaks.
OL,13,FThat boils down to around 169,000
OL,14,Fpeople without a seat each day.
OL,16,FAnd with rail prices continuing to
OL,17,Frise, so too is consumer anger.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
