OL,3,COverpaying for overcrowding? Almost a
OL,4,Cquarter of train users have to stand
OL,6,FRail passengers in London are least
OL,7,Flikely to get a seat, with around 27%
OL,8,Fof rail users standing during the
OL,9,Fmorning peak.
OL,11,FThe city with the largest increase in
OL,12,Fthe number of passengers standing up
OL,13,Fwas Birmingham, with one in ten left
OL,14,Fwithout a seat.
OL,16,FExperts have told ITV News that
OL,17,Fovercrowding is avoidable, and if rail
OL,18,Fproviders hopped on board with a few
OL,19,Fchanges, they could reduce the number
OL,20,Fof uncomfortable commuters.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
