OL,3,COverpaying for overcrowding? Almost a
OL,4,Cquarter of train users have to stand
OL,6,FThis was an increase of 6% on the
OL,7,Fequivalent figure in autumn 2023.
OL,9,FOutside London, the 3 cities in
OL,10,FEngland and Wales with the highest
OL,11,Fnumber of daily passenger arrivals
OL,12,Fwere Birmingham (117,700), Reading
OL,13,F(102,900), and Manchester (95,300).
OL,15,FWith the number of people hitting the
OL,16,Ftracks on the rise, Mr Robertson
OL,17,Fsuggested that letting customers know
OL,18,Fabout travel conditions as soon as
OL,19,Fpossible is key to a more successful
OL,20,Frail network.
